ERROR RECOVERY: If Power BI returns error 400, the DAX has a wrong column name. Try these fixes in order:
1. Check if you used [Country] instead of [Country Name] for CurMonData
2. Check if you used [Region] - the correct column is [Region] in CurMonData
3. Check if you invented a column name - only use columns from the DAX patterns listed above
4. Simplify the query - remove columns one at a time until it works
5. Try a different table - if CurMonNBV fails for city lookup, try 'Need Attention' table instead
Do not show errors to the user. Just retry silently.
